metadata.name: Abstract Symphony #33
metadata.description:
Abstract Symphony is a collection of chaos and beauties of our nature and psyche.

This artwork include 6 layers first of all 16 background and in second layer we have ink picture but  they will not be repeated in all the images. third and fourth layer are more than 30 paints. in last two layers we have noise and covers

metadata.name: fx_donutshops #336
Stoner Stick People Series 2 #33
metadata.description:
The other day I was finally inspired to pick up the Stoner Stick People and again venture off into places I hadn't been, trying new things. I wanted to do more than I'd done before, a promise to myself, and it took a minute for something to click. Color. Not just little bits, but entire environments, Vibes, for Stoners to just, well, Vibe in. The way I wanted to vibe. Be distracted and free my mind to go to the places where it needed to. Needs to.

Another experiment in learning how to layer and play with...lots, lol. I hope y'all enjoy Series 2 :)

Puff puff pass.

Wessel '22

metadata.name: Stoner Stick People #69
metadata.description:
I decided to put together a fun little project to dive into this section of the nft world to check out the possibilities using a concept I've played with before, stick people. The idea of how generative art can work for an artist and their process is an interesting one to me that hopefully I will get a chance to explore. Start basic, with smiles, and go from there, art :)

For all my stoner friends out there :)

Puff Puff Pass

Wessel '22

metadata.name: gimme all your love #287
metadata.description: Sometimes we feel so lost that we look for any way to find the ground beneath our feet again. Sometimes we try to feel something through other people, through looks, words, touches. This is a temporary cure, which sooner or later will stop helping.
